From: Sangwook Han <sangwook.han@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 11:52:44 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Run pure timer-core tests off-simulator (step 2/2)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

What: relocate the two pure timer-core test suites — the TimerState
pause/resume/complete/remaining-time transitions and
CompletedRelativeTimeFormatter (10 tests) — from the app-hosted
PTimerTests target into PTimerCoreTests, where they run on macOS via
`swift test` with no simulator. Removed from the app target.

Why: completes PTIMER-177. The pure timer rules now have off-simulator
unit tests; the TimerManager coordinator tests (RunLoop ticking, UIKit
feedback, notifications, persistence wiring) stay app-hosted because
they exercise the OS-facing layer that legitimately needs the app host.

Verified: PTimerCore `swift test` = 10 tests, no simulator; app-hosted
suite = 1464, 0 failures (was 1474 with the 10 still app-hosted).

PTIMER-177 Decouple the pure timer state machine from the UIKit-bound
           TimerManager

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
